          Unlock countless combinations and commands

          The Ring Bridge lets Ring Smart Lights, doorbells and cameras talk to each other and work better together. If one Ring Bridge-enabled device detects motion, it can turn on your Ring Smart Lights, activate your Ring cameras and more, giving your Ring of Security endless combinations. One Ring Bridge supported per household.

          Group lights together with the Ring Bridge to turn them all on whenever motion is detected. If one light sees something, it can brighten up a small pathway or make your whole yard shine.

          Pair with Ring Smart Lights to customize settings of individual lights or groups by adjusting their brightness, motion sensitivity, and the amount of time they stay on from the Ring app.

          Use the Ring Bridge to connect Ring Smart Lights with Ring doorbells and cameras to activate them whenever motion is detected.

          Connects your Ring Smart Lights to select Alexa-enabled devices to activate lighting and adjust settings at the sound of your voice. Want to turn on the backyard lights? Just ask Alexa.

          1. Install the Bridge & Lights

          Add batteries to your Ring Smart Lights, plug in the Ring Bridge indoors, then place lights throughout your yard.

          2. Connect to the Ring app

          Use the Ring Bridge to group Ring Smart Lighting together with the Ring app, and connect to your home Wi-Fi network to customize settings.

          3. Expand your Ring of Security

          The Ring Bridge allows Ring Smart Lights to connect with Ring doorbells, cameras and select Alexa-enabled devices to create a fully connected home security system.

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

            5.0 out of 5 stars needs a hard reset each time you unplug
            Reviewed in the United States on July 23, 2019
            Verified Purchase
            Recently bought the bridge that was included as a package with the wired floodright promo during prime day. Since i already have the ring doorbell pro, i already had the app. Im aware of the issues of both floodlight and bridge so when setting up, it was fairly a breeze. When I hooked up my wired floodlight, I had to relocate the bridge on a different location. Thats when i started having connectivity issues. Either the bridge could not connect to my wifi (which was less than 4ft from my router) or the floodlight! After a hard reset, it went smoothly and the floodlight was able to link up properly. But because i had to detach my floodlight from the mount, the bridge again could NOT connect?! I had to hard reset the bridge again. The floodlight was then able to link to the bridge.

            If this is the only way to link your smart lights to the bridge, then it would be a pain to reset the bridge and add each of your lights. Also, the reason, that many people will purchase this , is to "link" other Ring products. I was able to set notifications for motion and light and activate the doorbell each time floodlight is activated. This is NOT possible to link other smart objects (like my Arlo cams).

            UPDATE: I am updating my rating for the RING Bridge. I had shut down my power from breaker many times already and didnt encounter an issue that I had to reset my bridge. Ive since added and linked my Ring Transformer and sensor and the bridge is doing its job to integrate and communicate among the Ring products that I have.
